"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802765","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-13","<p>A list of all parties consulted will be published as part of the S4C ​review.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-12-13T10:28:49.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802765/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802765/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802765/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-07","S4C Independent Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether a list of those invited to submit evidence to the S4C Review will be published as part of the S4C Review.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","118314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802766","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-15","<p>Although the future trading relationship with the EU is subject to negotiations, we are committed to minimising disruption and giving as much certainty as possible. That’s why the Government is pursuing a time-limited implementation period to allow business the time they need to adapt to new arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>Government will be working alongside trade associations and others to communicate to businesses the changes in the UKs trading relationship with the EU, ensuring that they are ready for Day One of exit regardless of the outcome of the negotiations.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","118099","2017-12-15T11:17:48.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802766/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802766/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802766/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-07","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department has prepared a plan to assist small businesses in the event that the UK leaves the EU without a deal on the future trading relationship.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","118315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802767","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>The government is committed to ensuring that all children, regardless of background, get the best possible start in life. Children’s centres have an important role to play.</p><p> </p><p>I am aware of the previous commitment made to consult on the future of children’s centre services. However, we rightly want to take some time to gather evidence and consider what steps would be appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>Local councils continue to have a duty to ensure there are sufficient centres or other settings such as family hubs to meet local need and to consult where they plan to make changes to local provision.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-12T17:39:38.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802767/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802767/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802767/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-07","Children's Centres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether it is her policy to conduct a consultation into children's centres.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","118316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802768","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-21","<p>Defra is working closely with the Food Standards Agency, the Devolved Administrations and the veterinary sector to ensure that both the Government and veterinary businesses can continue to protect animal health and welfare, public health and food safety, and enable trade in animals and animal products. Together, we are assessing the challenges and opportunities arising from leaving the EU, with the aim of developing a flexible and skilled workforce which meets the UK’s needs for both the immediate and longer term future. The Shortage Occupation List is based on expert advice to the Home Office from the independent Migration Advisory Committee and is reviewed regularly.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-21T13:18:58.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802768/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802768/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802768/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-07","Veterinary Medicine: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will add veterinarians working in the UK’s agri-food sector to the shortage occupation list after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","118317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802769","Ministry of Defence","true","2017-12-15","<p>The following entities which come within the Ministry of Defence (MOD) boundary are required to lay reports before Parliament:</p><p> </p><p>Armed Forces' Pay Review Body</p><p>Defence Equipment and Support</p><p>Defence Electronics and Components Agency</p><p>Defence Science and Technology Laboratory</p><p>Greenwich Hospital and Travers Foundation</p><p>National Army Museum</p><p>National Employer Advisory Board</p><p>National Museum of the Royal Navy</p><p>Reserve Forces and Cadets Associations</p><p>Royal Air Force Museum</p><p><ins class="ministerial">Royal Hospital Chelsea</ins></p><p>Service Complaints Ombudsman</p><p>Single Source Regulations Office</p><p>United Kingdom Hydrographic Office</p><p> </p><p>A list of the bodies for which the MOD is responsible can be found on the gov.uk website and in the MOD Annual Report and Accounts 2016-17 (HC 21) at Note 22.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-12-15T14:48:27.653Z","2017-12-21T17:41:57.253Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802769/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802769/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802769/answer","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802769/answer/previousversion/30060","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-07","Ministry of Defence: Non-departmental Public Bodies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what bodies for which his Department is responsible are required to lay reports before Parliament.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802770","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-14","<p>It will take some time to gather the information required to answer the hon. Member's question.</p><p>I will write to the hon. Member and a copy of my letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-12-14T10:55:53.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802770/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802770/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802770/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-07","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel of visiting forces are based in the UK; what nations those forces come from; and what the locations are of visiting units.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802771","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-22","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union, working with officials across Government, is carrying out a programme of rigorous and extensive analytical work that will contribute to our exit negotiations with the EU, to define our future partnership with the EU, and to inform our understanding of how EU exit will affect the UK’s domestic policies and frameworks.</p><p> </p><p>This includes engaging extensively with the millions of small and medium sized businesses throughout Britain who make an enormous contribution to our country. The Government continues to speak widely and regularly with these businesses and representative bodies such as the Federation of Small Businesses (FSB) in order to secure the best possible deal for the United Kingdom.</p><p> </p><p>In July, the FSB hosted a small business roundtable attended by Government Ministers. The FSB are also regularly invited to the Business Advisory Group, a forum of business representative organisations who regularly meet with senior Cabinet Ministers, including DExEU Secretary of State David Davis, to highlight their concerns regarding EU exit. Most recently, on 7 December I attended a discussion of the SME Advisory Board, hosted by my colleague Margot James in the Department for Business, Energy &amp; Industrial Strategy to discuss the effect of our exit on small and medium sized businesses.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-12-22T15:06:51.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802771/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802771/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802771/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-07","Small Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether his Department intends to conduct an impact assessment of the effect on small businesses of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","118320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802772","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-14","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility’s (OBR) latest Economic and Fiscal Outlook was published on 22 November 2017 and is available at the following address: <a href="http://cdn.budgetresponsibility.org.uk/Nov2017EFOwebversion-2.pdf" target="_blank">http://cdn.budgetresponsibility.org.uk/Nov2017EFOwebversion-2.pdf</a>. This sets out forecasts of the UK economy and public finances to 2022-23, which extends well beyond the point at which the UK leaves the EU.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-12-14T17:12:04.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802772/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802772/answer","Nov2017EFOwebversion-2.pdf","OBR Economic and Fiscal Outlook November 2017","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802772/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-07","Economic Situation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, with reference to his oral evidence to the Exiting the EU Committee on 6 December 2017, whether the Office for Budget Responsibility forecast of the economic impact of withdrawal from the EU is in the public domain.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","118321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802774","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) has undertaken a procurement exercise for the provision of apprenticeship training to non-levy employers from January 2018 to March 2019.</p><p> </p><p>This will ensure that small and medium sized enterprises can access high quality apprenticeship training to support their growth and success.</p><p> </p><p>The ESFA notified bidders of the outcome of the process on 7 December 2017, but as this remains a live procurement, we are unable to comment further. The department will provide further information in due course.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-12-12T17:29:25.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802774/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802774/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802774/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-07","Apprentices: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she plans to provide information to apprenticeship providers on the allocation of funding for apprentice places for 2018-19.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","118322"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802776","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>To inform our policies, we commission, use and assess a range of data and information, which has included analysis of average profit margins for providers.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-12-12T16:26:31.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802776/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802776/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802776/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-07","Apprentices: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the margins of profitability of apprenticeship training provided by government-funded providers.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","118323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802777","Home Office","false","2017-12-12","<p>Recruitment of an additional 300 Border Force officers is underway. The Government has been clear that this additional resource will be dedicated to undertaking work to prepare for changes brought about by Brexit.</p><p> </p><p>Border Force is ensuring flexibility in recruitment plans to ensure the approach can be flexed and adapted as future requirements become clearer.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-12-12T17:47:55.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802777/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802777/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802777/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-07","UK Border Force: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 23 November 2017 to Question 114587, what the evidential basis is for her Department's conclusion that an additional 300 Border Force officers is adequate in preparation for when the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","118324"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802779","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-14","<p>Radioactive materials are used in a wide range of equipment (e.g. in small quantities for radioluminescent light sources). Therefore this information is not held centrally, it could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-12-14T17:47:38.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802779/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802779/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802779/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-07","Ministry of Defence: Radioactive Materials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, at which sites managed by his Department radioactive materials are stored, and at which such sites radioactive materials were previously stored during the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118325"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802780","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>The study of early education and development (SEED) findings (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/early-years-provision-quality" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/early-years-provision-quality</a>) indicate that improvements in the quality of early years provision have been seen over time. The research showed no variation in quality by area deprivation. Furthermore, the regional variation seen is not indicative of low overall quality in any region.</p><p> </p><p>The research backs up what we know – the number of childcare providers now rated good or outstanding by Ofsted has risen to 94% (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-providers-and-inspections-as-at-31-august-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/childcare-providers-and-inspections-as-at-31-august-2017</a>) and the attainment gap between disadvantaged children and their peers continues to close at age 5.</p><p> </p><p>The early years workforce strategy published in 2017, sets out government's plans to help employers attract, retain and develop early years staff to support delivery of high quality provision.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-12T17:41:55.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802780/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802780/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802780/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-07","Pre-school Education: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to pages 91-97 of her Department's Study of Early Education and Development (SEED): Study of Quality of Early Years Provision in England, published in December 2017, what steps her Department is taking to end regional variations in quality in early education.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","118326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802782","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>The 2018-19 funding allocations to local councils for delivering 30 hours of free childcare will be announced later in December 2017.</p><p><em><br> </em></p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-12T17:37:25.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802782/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802782/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802782/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-07","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many local authorities will receive (a) less, (b) more and (c) the same funding in 2018-19 than in 2017-18 for delivering the 30 hours of funded childcare policy.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","118327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802783","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-13","<p>The Department for International Development supports the education, health and agriculture sectors across Cameroon through regional programmes and multilateral partners. The British Government does not provide specific support to Anglophone citizens. Our High Commissioner in Yaoundé has been following events in the Anglophone regions closely and has actively raised the need for dialogue and restraint with the Cameroonian authorities, including their obligations under international law in respect to human rights. We continue to call for restraint, for all parties to reject violence, pursue dialogue and urgently take action to reduce tensions.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-12-13T14:46:18.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802783/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802783/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802783/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-07","Cameroon: Politics and Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign Commonwealth Affairs, what support is being made available to Anglophone citizens of Cameroon.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","118328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802785","Home Office","false","2017-12-12","<p>The Prime Minister has been clear of the UK’s unconditional commitment to continued cooperation with the EU to preserve UK and European security, to fight terrorism and to uphold justice across Europe.</p><p> </p><p>As set out in the recent ‘<em>Security, Law Enforcement and Criminal Justice – a future partnership paper’</em> published on 18 September, the UK has proposed a bold new strategic partnership with the EU that provides a comprehensive framework for our future security, law enforcement and criminal justice cooperation to deliver the capabilities our operational partners need to keep our people safe.</p><p> </p><p>Our EU cooperation is also part of a wider landscape of international counter terrorism work, which includes cooperation through relationships such as Interpol, the Five Eyes, and bilateral work with individual countries.</p><p> </p><p>The details of our future relationship with the EU, including cooperation through our agencies will be subject to negotiation. Public safety in the UK and the rest of Europe is a top priority and will be at the heart of this aspect of our negotiations.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-12-12T17:54:34.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802785/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802785/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802785/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-07","Intelligence Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what her policy is on ensuring that British security services and crime agencies continue to share intelligence and work with their EU counterparts once the UK has left the EU.","false","Biography information for Damien Moore","Southport","Damien Moore","118329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802786","Scotland Office","false","2017-12-14","<p>The total spend of the Scotland Office on hospitality since May 2015 is as follows:</p><p> </p><p><strong>2015-2016</strong> £ 8,987.00</p><p><strong>2016-2017</strong> £ 453.35</p><p> </p><p>The 2015-16 figure includes food and drink spend for both events and hospitality, as these were not recorded separately. From 2016, events spend has been recorded separately to hospitality spend. This is reflected in the figures above.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-12-14T15:30:17.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802786/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802786/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802786/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-12-07","Scotland Office: Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what estimate he has made of the expenditure of (a) his Department, (b) its agencies and (c) its non-departmental public bodies on hospitality since 7 May 2015.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802788","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-13","<p>As part of our preparations to leave the EU, we are in the process of carrying out a programme of analytical work that will contribute to our understanding of how withdrawal from the EU will affect the UK.</p><p> </p><p>The Queen’s Speech announced that an Agriculture Bill will be introduced during this session of Parliament. The Bill will allow us to deliver our manifesto commitment to provide stability to farmers, supporting the industry to compete domestically and on the global market, and will allow us to grow more, sell more and export more great British food. We are committed to getting the best possible deal that allows us to continue to have tariff-free and frictionless access for goods and services into the European market. We will also strike new trade deals around the world to help farmers take advantage of the growing appetite for Great British food.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-13T12:40:06.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802788/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802788/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802788/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-07","Agricultural Products: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the UK leaving the EU on farm gate prices.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802789","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-12-14","<p>I have regular discussions with my colleagues at the Home Office on a wide range of topics of mutual interest.</p><p> </p><p>Although the changes business will face - as a result of the UK’s exit from the EU - are subject to negotiations with our EU partners, we want to achieve the best possible outcome and the strongest possible partnership - one that works for UK businesses.</p><p> </p><p>We already have highly efficient processes for freight arriving from the rest of the world – the vast majority of customs declarations in the UK are submitted electronically and are cleared rapidly.</p><p> </p><p>However, we are committed to minimising disruption and giving as much certainty as possible. That’s why the Government is pursuing a time-limited implementation period to allow business the time they need to adapt to new arrangements.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-12-14T11:34:10.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802789/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802789/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802789/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-07","UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with the Home Secretary regarding the Border Force preparations being made to minimise the disruption to small business supply chains after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","118332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802791","Prime Minister","false","2017-12-11","<p>Details of Ministerial meetings with external organisations and individuals are published quarterly and made available on the gov.uk website.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-12-11T16:51:37.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802791/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802791/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802791/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-12-07","City of London Corporation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what discussions her Office has had with the City of London Corporation since July 2016.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802792","Department for Education","false","2017-12-12","<p>Our delivery contractor, Childcare Works, is currently in discussion with local councils, including some of our early delivery areas, about potential buddying matches. Once the matches have been officially confirmed, this information will be made publically available.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-12-12T17:42:52.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802792/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802792/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802792/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-07","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she plans to provide the details of local authorities involved in the buddy system for delivering the 30 hours of funded childcare policy.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","118334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802794","Prime Minister","false","2017-12-11","<p>Our discussions were constructive.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-12-11T16:52:47.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802794/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802794/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802794/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-12-07","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if she will publish the transcripts of her discussions with the Democratic Unionist Party leader, Arlene Foster on the UK's negotiations with the EU.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802796","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-14","<p>A list of where Ministry of Defence buildings are located is attached.</p><p>The running cost for each building used by the Ministry of Defence is not held centrally.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-12-14T17:47:12.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802796/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802796/answer","118336 - MOD Building Locations.docx","118336 - MOD Building Locations","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802796/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-07","Ministry of Defence: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) location is and (b) running costs are for each building used by his Department., excluding operational bases.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802797","Scotland Office","false","2017-12-14","<p>The cost of running the Scotland Office buildings in 2016-17 was as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Melville Crescent</strong></p></td><td><p>£253,217</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Dover House </strong></p></td><td><p>£601,456</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-12-14T15:31:14.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802797/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802797/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802797/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-12-07","Scotland Office: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland,what the running costs are for each building used by his Department.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802799","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-21","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is currently located in the following existing Government buildings:</p><ul><ul><li><p>9 Downing Street and 70 Whitehall;</p></li><li><p>MOD Main Building, Whitehall;</p></li><li><p>1 Horse Guards Road;</p></li><li><p>100 Parliament Street</p></li></ul></ul><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The running costs for the 17/18 financial year to the end of November (excluding VAT) are:</p><ul><ul><li><p>9 Downing Street and 70 Whitehall - £682,550</p></li><li><p>MOD, Whitehall - £1,763,667</p></li><li><p>1 Horse Guards Road - £165,984</p></li><li><p>As of the end of November, no costs had been paid to HMRC for occupancy within 100 Parliament Street</p></li></ul></ul><p><strong> </strong></p><p>These figures are in-line with the going market rates for rent and operation in Westminster.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-12-21T12:35:58.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802799/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802799/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802799/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union,what the (a) location is and (b) running costs are for each building used by his Department.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802800","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-12-13","<p>Reports about harassment of BBC Persian staff and their families in Iran are deeply worrying. The Foreign Secretary specifically raised our concerns about the harassment of BBC Persian staff and their families in Iran with his Iranian counterpart during his visit to Tehran on 9-10 December. This issue is intimately bound up with wider questions of the protection of civil and political rights in Iran; the Foreign Secretary also raised our broader concerns on Iran’s human rights record during his visit.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2017-12-13T17:54:47.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802800/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802800/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802800/answer","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802800/answer/previousversion/28780","Biography information for Alistair Burt","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-07","Iran: BBC Persian Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to his oral contribution of 21 November 2017, Official Report, Vol 631 Col 852, if will raise persecution of and intimidation against staff of the BBC Persian service during his forthcoming visit to Iran.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","118339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802801","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-12-20","<p>Please see the attached spreadsheet, which details the information requested.</p><p> </p><p>This has been interpreted to be Core Defra occupations only, excluding its Executive Agencies &amp; the Non-Departmental Public Bodies (NDPB’s). Where buildings are part occupied, only the Core Defra proportion of total gross site costs are included.</p><p> </p><p>We have reduced the number of buildings occupied by Core Defra from 29 to 26 since 2010. Running costs have fallen by a quarter, from £35,525,000 to £26,793,000 over the same period.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-12-20T16:44:00.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802801/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802801/answer","Copy of Core Defra Building Running Costs.xlsx","Defra Building costs","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802801/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-12-07","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the (a) location is and (b) running costs are for each building used by his Department.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802803","Department of Health","false","2017-12-12","<p>The data is not available in the format requested.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-12T17:00:05.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802803/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802803/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802803/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-07","Health Visitors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many full-time equivalent health visitors work in each local authority area, and how many such visitors there were before responsibility was transferred from the Department of Health.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","118341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802804","Department for Transport","false","2017-12-14","<p>Two rail franchises are currently required to provide limited Boxing Day services. Greater Anglia is required to operate certain services between London Liverpool Street and Stansted Airport. Govia Thameslink Railway is required to operate certain services between London Victoria, Gatwick Airport and Brighton, between London Victoria and Sutton, and between London Victoria and East Croydon. During any periods of engineering work, replacement bus services would be provided.</p><p> </p><p>All franchises have discretion to operate Boxing Day services on a commercial basis, subject to agreement with Network Rail.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-12-14T14:50:54.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802804/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802804/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802804/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-12-07","Railways: Public Holidays","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which rail franchises are required to provide train services on Boxing Day, and what those requirements are for each franchise.","false","Biography information for John Grogan","Keighley","John Grogan","118342"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802806","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-12-15","<p>To answer this question, an accident has been defined as an incident involving another vessel. There have been two accidents in the last five years. A UK submarine was involved in an incident with the Fishing Vessel KAREN on 15 April 2015 and HMS AMBUSH (Astute Class) collided with a Merchant Vessel on 20 July 2016.</p><p>I am withholding further information as its disclosure would, or would be likely to, prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-12-15T13:21:57.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802806/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802806/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802806/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-12-07","Submarines: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many accidents Royal Navy submarines have been involved in the past five years, broken down by (a) class of submarine and (b) severity of accident.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","118343"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797676","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-07","<p><strong>At the request of the Prime Minister, the Committee on Standards in Public Life (CSPL) is currently carrying out a review of the intimidation of Parliamentary candidates, including those who stood at the 2017 General Election. The Committee will be publishing its report ‘Intimidation in Public Life: A Review by the Committee on Standards in Public Life’ on Wednesday 13 December. The Government will consider the report and its recommendations carefully.</strong></p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-12-07T10:30:30.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797676/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797676/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/797676/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-06","General Election 2017","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government plans to undertake a comprehensive investigation of intimidation of candidates and canvassers during the 2017 General Election.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","116639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800981","Home Office","false","2017-12-11","<p>Burma is currently on the visa national list and nationals of Burma therefore need to apply for a visa in advance of travel to the UK. All applications for visas are considered on an individual basis.</p><p> </p><p>Individuals subject to a UN or EU travel ban will be automatically refused a UK visa or leave to enter the UK should they be encountered at the border.</p><p> </p><p>The UK keeps its visa system under regular review. Decisions on changes are always taken in the round, and reflect key facets of the bilateral relationship with the country concerned. The Government is monitoring the situation in Burma.</p><p> </p><p>There are currently no plans to change the visa policy for individuals from Burma.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-12-11T11:42:51.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800981/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800981/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800981/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-06","Travel Restrictions: Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the Government policy is on introducing visa bans on military personnel from Burma.","false","Biography information for Gill Furniss","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Gill Furniss","117540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800989","Department of Health","false","2017-12-12","<p>The information on the average number of times an ambulance has been called to a prison, and the average number of incidents of a prisoner attending accident and emergency departments at local general hospitals is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>In February 2013, the National Offender Management Service (NOMS) (now HM Prison and Probation Service) issued guidance to prisons and immigration removal centres operated by NOMS concerning emergency ambulance call-outs. This guidance, Prison Service Instruction (PSI) 03/2013 Medical Emergency Response Codes outlines the medical symptoms in a prisoner, for which a prison must always call out an emergency ambulance. This PSI is mandatory in all prisons in England.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","117552","2017-12-12T14:36:24.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800989/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800989/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/800989/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-06","Prisons: Ambulance Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average number of times is that ambulances have been called to prisons in England and Wales per prison since March 2017.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","117548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801158","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-13","<p>The Government and the Information Commissioner recognise the challenges facing organisations across the UK in their preparations for the Data Protection Bill and the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). There are already resources on the Commissioner's website (ico.org.uk) to help organisations employing fewer than 250 people, including parish councils, prepare. The Commissioner has launched a dedicated helpline service for smaller organisations and has updated its 'SME toolkit' to reflect the requirements of the GDPR. The Commissioner will also be simplifying her &quot;12-step&quot; GDPR preparation guidance in response to feedback from small and micro-enterprises and will continue to develop further guidance on both the Bill and GDPR.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2017-12-13T16:22:34.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801158/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801158/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/801158/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-06","Parish Councils: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, whether her Department has issued guidance to parish councils on compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation.","false","Biography information for James Cartlidge","South Suffolk","James Cartlidge","117717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802081","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-15","<p>At Budget, the Chancellor announced that from April 2018, Housing Benefit claimants will receive an additional two weeks’ support during their transition to Universal Credit (UC), providing them with extra support at a time of change in their lives.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is also making it easier for claimants to have the housing element of their UC award paid directly to their landlord, ensuring that UC claimants are supported throughout their transition into work.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-12-15T11:47:17.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802081/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802081/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802081/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-06","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Minister of State for Housing and Planning on the potential effect of the roll-out of universal credit on people seeking housing benefits.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","117768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802082","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-15","<p>Universal Credit (UC) has already been successful in getting more people into work by ensuring that work always pays, and that has boosted household incomes. UC claimants are four percentage points more likely to be in work within six months than a matched sample of Jobseeker’s Allowance claimants.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2017-12-15T11:45:36.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802082/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802082/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802082/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-06","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with Secretary of State for Work and Pensions on the potential effect of the the roll-out of universal credit on levels of household income.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","117769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802083","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-14","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) are not able to identify the exact number of people who paid their self assessment tax demand at a branch of the post office in the last 12 months. Individuals can make payments to HMRC multiple times a year, and sometimes do so using different payment methods.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-12-14T14:46:46.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802083/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802083/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802083/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-06","Taxation: Self-assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people paid their self-assessment tax demand at a branch of the Post Office in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","117770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802084","HM Treasury","false","2017-12-14","<p>The facility to pay HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) at the Post Office in its current format is being withdrawn by the service provider Santander. HMRC are not the only users of this service and had no influence on this decision or the timing of the withdrawal.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2017-12-14T16:22:41.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802084/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802084/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802084/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-06","Taxation: Self-assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether his Department undertook a consultation on the use of the Post Office to pay self assessment tax bills ahead of the decision to remove that service on 15 December 2017.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","117771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802085","Home Office","false","2017-12-11","<p>The Prime Minister has proposed that there should be an Implementation Period immediately after the UK leaves the EU, while we and the EU put in place the necessary preparations for the future arrangements, and to ensure that people and businesses only have to plan for one set of changes. During this time, EU citizens will continue to be able to come and live and work in the UK. But there will be a registration system - an essential preparation for the new regime.</p><p>There are a wide range of options as to how EU migration might work after that Period. We are considering these options very carefully and we will take decisions based on evidence. As part of this, on 27 July, the Government commissioned the Migration Advisory Committee (MAC) to gather evidence on patterns of EU migration and the role of migration in the wider economy, ahead of our exit from the EU. We have asked the MAC to report by September 2018 and flagged that interim reports throughout the period would be helpful to our input into our developing policies.</p><p>The Government will be setting out initial proposals for our future immigration arrangements shortly.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-12-11T17:14:31.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802085/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802085/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802085/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-06","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what immigration rules will apply to EU nationals who are (a) sportspeople, (b) coaches and (c) supporters after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","117772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802086","Department of Health","false","2017-12-14","<p>Allocations for Sexual Assault Referral Centres have increased this year. This has enabled NHS England to increase the number of specialists working across the London Havens, specialist centres supporting survivors of sexual assault in the London area. This includes an increase in counselling and therapy team capacity, and the creation of social work liaison posts.</p><p> </p><p>Together with the Mayor’s Office for Policing and Crime, NHS England have been working on a Child House pilot. This is a new integrated health, social care and criminal justice service for child victims of sexual abuse in the north central London area. This service is expected to open in 2018. The pilot will evaluate whether the Child House model is effective in the London context and explore whether the model should be rolled out across the whole of London.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-12-14T16:49:33.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802086/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802086/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802086/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-06","Sexual Assault Referral Centres: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to provide support to survivors of sexual assault in London when services are over-subscribed.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","117773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802087","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-12-11","<p>The independent review of Full Time Social Action is due to make recommendations to Government by the end of December 2017. The Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport will respond to these recommendations in the New Year.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-12-11T14:15:37.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802087/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802087/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802087/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-12-06","Charities: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, when her Department plans to respond to the consultation on the Full-time social action review.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","117774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802088","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-18","<p>EU citizens can vote in local elections in the UK.The Government was clear from the start of withdrawal negotiations that EU citizens in the UK and UK citizens in the EU should have their voting and candidacy rights protected.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-12-18T16:15:47.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802088/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802088/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802088/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-06","Voting Rights: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what Government policy is on EU citizens voting in local elections in the UK.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","117775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802089","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-20","<p>Our policy on prisoner voting is well established – this Government will not allow convicted offenders behind bars to vote.</p><p> </p><p>At the same time, we are addressing an anomaly which allows those offenders on Home Detention Curfew to vote but not offenders who are released on temporary licence.</p><p> </p><p>Under the changes, up to a hundred offenders on short sentences, released on temporary licence into the community within twelve months of sentencing will be eligible to vote if an election is called during that period.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-12-20T11:15:40.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802089/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802089/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802089/answer","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802089/answer/previousversion/30114","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-06","Prisoners: Voting Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the Government's policy is on voting rights for prisoners with short sentences.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","117776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802090","Department for Education","false","2017-12-13","<p>In the last 12 months (December 2016 to November 2017), the Student Loans Company (SLC) has responded to 93.5% of Stage 1 complaints within the advertised 15 day response time.</p><p> </p><p>When measured from the start of this financial year (2017-18), the SLC has responded to 96.9% of Stage 1 complaints within the advertised response time.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-12-13T20:22:13.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802090/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802090/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802090/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-12-06","Student Loans Company: Complaints","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of complaints to the Student Loan Company have been dealt with in the advertised timescale in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","117777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802091","Women and Equalities","false","2017-12-15","<p>My Rt hon. Friend the Minister for Women and Equalities became responsible for the Gender Recognition Act 2004 on 16 November 2017, following a ‘Machinery of Government’ change.</p><p>The government has committed to carrying out a broad consultation on the Gender Recognition Act to look at making the process of legally changing gender less bureaucratic and intrusive for transgender people.</p><p>We will encourage employers to respond to the consultation.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-12-15T14:18:38.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802091/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802091/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802091/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-12-06","Gender Recognition","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of the implementation of the Gender Recognition Act in the workplace.","false","Biography information for Tonia Antoniazzi","Gower","Tonia Antoniazzi","117778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802092","Cabinet Office","false","2017-12-13","<p>No Ministers from the Cabinet Office have received representations from Bell Pottinger on behalf of Atos IT Services UK Limited, Centrica PLC or Ernst &amp; Young.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-12-13T14:31:04.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802092/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802092/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802092/answer","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802092/answer/previousversion/28635","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-06","Cabinet Office: Bell Pottinger Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what representations any Minister of his Department has received from Bell Pottinger on behalf of (a) Atos IT Services UK Limited, (b) Centrica PLC and (c) Ernst & Young.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","117779"
