"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802096","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-12-15","<p>Ministers from the Department for Exiting the European Union have not have organised and undertaken more than 400 recorded engagements with business and civil society stakeholders since July 2016.</p><p>Details of Ministerial meetings are published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns on GOV.UK.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-12-15T14:54:47.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802096/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802096/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/802096/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-12-06","Department for Exiting the European Union: Bell Pottinger Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what representations any Minister of his Department has received from Bell Pottinger on behalf of (a) Atos IT Services UK Limited, (b) Centrica PLC, (c) DS Smith plc, (d) Ernst & Young, (e) Heads of the Valleys Development Company Limited and (f) Monarch Holdings Limited.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","117783"
